  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/assets/82375995/10c2a3c2-f2a4-4df5-8618-7515c21e033b)\r\n\r\nhttps://ci.status.im/job/status-desktop/job/systems/job/linux/job/x86_64/job/tests-e2e-new/124/allure/#suites/85aa51e65eb2606a1f89f1dfcae42139/8ba337a35d9d993b/\r\n\r\nSometimes autotest encounters that logging out from the app takes longer than 10 seconds. I am not sure which timeout is acceptable though. In app logs i clearly see the logging out was initiated\r\n\r\n```\r\ntid=1703015 file=core.nim:27 rpc_method=wallet_getOwnedCollectiblesAsync\r\nINF 2023-12-14 04:36:32.267+00:00 shutting down...                           topics=\"status-app\" tid=1703015 file=nim_status_client.nim:173\r\nINF 2023-12-14 04:36:32.267+00:00 logging out...                             topics=\"app-controller\" tid=1703015 file=app_controller.nim:288\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever the verification i do (checking if process no longer exists within 10 seconds) sometimes fails, which means the process is still running.\r\n\r\nI need a hand here to investigate and perhaps define applicable timeframe for this action. It looks like regression to me now \r\n\r\n",
